<h3>Getting here by car</h3>

<p>
    The venue is a <a href="https://goo.gl/maps/jRzqy6E4QSL2">short drive</a> from M11 junction 11.
    There is limited free parking on site, but the <a href="http://bit.ly/2rjVoHY">public car parks on the Addenbrooke's site</a> are all within a few minutes walking distance.
</p>

<p>
    Alternatively, parking is available at the <a href="http://www.cambridgeparkandride.info/trumpington.shtml">Trumpington Park and Ride</a>, with a bus to Addenbrooke's hospital.
</p>

<br />
<h3>Getting here by train</h3>

<p>
    Cambridge railway station is located just over a mile away from the venue.
    It is a <a href="https://goo.gl/maps/y5rRq7WJTJQ2">straightforward walk</a> (approx. 30 mins) to the venue.
</p>

<p>
    Alternatively, the <a href="https://tiscon-maps-stagecoachbus.s3.amazonaws.com/Timetables/East/CAMBRIDGE/CA%20-%20CITI%201%20-%20JAN%202017.pdf">Citi 1</a> bus towards Fulbourn can be caught from stop 2 outside the station.
</p>

